<TITLE> PM to launch job scheme Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, May 5 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina is set to launch a project called 'national service' in Barguna district on Thursday, devised to create jobs for the unemployed. Barguna deputy commissioner Swapan Kumar said the prime minister would hand over appointment letters to four persons to inaugurate the project. About 4,000 unemployed youths in Barguna will get jobs under the project, which will be launched in other districts in phases. After inaugurating the project, she will also address a public meeting at the Barguna circuit house premises at around 2pm. Barguna youth development officials said in the first phase, youths in Barguna, Kurigram and Gopalganj would be provided with jobs under the project. They said a list of 13,734 people, aged between 18 and 35 having passed SSC exams, in five upazilas of the district, has been selected for the jobs. Initially, 800 people from each upazila will be given jobs after training. They will get a daily allowance of Tk 100 during the three-month training. On completion, they will be paid Tk 200 a day over a period of two years. Binoy Ranjan Mitra, assistant director of Barguna district youth development, told journalists that candidates with higher education and children of freedom fighters would get priority. State minister for youth and sports Md Ahad Ali Sarkar is expected to preside over the inauguration. The meeting is set to be addressed by state minister for local government, rural development and cooperatives Jahangir Kabir Nanak, state minister for religious affairs Shahjahan Mia and state minister for water resources Md Mahbubur Rahman. bdnew
